  <eligibility>
    <criteria>
      <textblock>
        Inclusion Criteria:

          -  Patients with the range of 15-50 years old

               -  Who were suspicious to opioid overdoses based on history and having clinical
                  appearance such as miotic pupils with loss of consciousness

               -  Give response to naloxone with increasing the level of consciousness

        Exclusion Criteria:

          -  Not giving response to naloxone and suspicious to have another reason for loss of
             consciousness
      </textblock>
    </criteria>
